Global Phytonutrients Market Insights
Phytonutrients Market size was valued at USD 40.1 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 66.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Phytonutrients Market Overview
The global phytonutrients market was valued at approximately USD 8.91 billion in 2024, with expectations to reach USD 14.03 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.7%. The rising consumer demand for natural, plant-based ingredients, combined with the increasing awareness of health benefits associated with phytonutrients, is expected to drive this market growth. Factors such as the increasing prevalence of chronic diseases, coupled with rising health-consciousness among individuals, further enhance the consumption of phytonutrient-rich products. The food & beverage and dietary supplements industries hold significant shares in the phytonutrients market, along with a rising demand for organic food products.

